
[1]kiln

   KILN, n. kil.

   1. A large stove or oven; a fabric of brick or stone which may be
   heated for the purpose of hardening, burning or drying any thing; as a
   kiln for baking or hardening earthen vessels; a kiln for drying grain
   or meal.

   2. A pile of brick constructed for burning or hardening; called also a
   brick-kiln.
